changesets": ["eddd26a54b2101c4334e091454a06a367187225e"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "26956": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020308 - Handle small double constants correctly in AddIsANonZeroAdditionOf / DefinitelyDifferentValue.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nNot optimizing doubles that don't fit in an int32 is the simplest fix and matches\nwhat we do in `DefinitelyDifferentValue`.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307257\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307705\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/ion/bug2020308.js", "js/src/jit/MIR.cpp"], "git_node": "c1a57db6b7a04b7f7c95f5018f437db6e1dbdabe", "git_parents": ["eddd26a54b2101c4334e091454a06a367187225e"], "node": "7bfb179f92c9231d2e74015ee0c22cf1331a43ae", "parents": ["063d4e461807aa4512df3305dda26a3f98a419a5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1781856592, "git_changesets": ["c1a57db6b7a04b7f7c95f5018f437db6e1dbdabe"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "26957": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2047553 - Disable `-Wstringop-overread` if compiling with GCC  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nGCC considers the size of `constexpr mozilla::Span` to `0` and that\ncauses the following warning which is treated as error.\n```\n/usr/include/c++/10/bits/stl_algobase.h:105:32: error: 'int __builtin_memcmp_eq(const void*, const void*, long unsigned int)' specified bound 20 exceeds source size 0 [-Werror=stringop-overread]\n  return __builtin_memcmp(__first1, __first2, sizeof(_Tp) * __num);\n         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n```\nI don't know why this is caused by unifying\n`TestFormattingAndStreaming.cpp` because it does not use `Span`.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307209\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307678\n", "files": ["mfbt/tests/gtest/moz.build"], "git_node": "56d057b2d0c72133c023c8e3a372d87bd523e45f", "git_parents": ["c1a57db6b7a04b7f7c95f5018f437db6e1dbdabe"], "node": "b157c4bcc101a494b124a20de809e0e14a5b4129", "parents": ["7bfb179f92c9231d2e74015ee0c22cf1331a43ae"], "tags": []}], "date": 1781856644, "git_changesets": ["56d057b2d0c72133c023c8e3a372d87bd523e45f"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "26958": {"changesets": [{"author": "sarah541 \u003csarahkhan1107@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2048297 - Show the full remaining bracket in the sports widget from the quarter-finals  a=pascalc\n\nIn the no-team (bracket-wide) pager, keep the focused decided-only reveal through\nthe group stage and Round of 16: only the active round and the next round's\nalready-decided fixtures show, and the final / third-place are not pinned, so the\nearly rounds don't fill with cards for matches weeks away or \"TBD vs TBD\"\nplaceholders.\n\nOnce the active round is the quarter-finals or later, surface the active round and\nevery later round the response carries - including not-yet-determined ones (a\nTBD-vs-TBD semi-final while the quarter-finals are live) - through to the final.\nThe final and third-place therefore only appear from the quarter-finals onward;\nBRACKET_FINISHING_STAGES is OR'd into the endgame filter so the third-place card\nstill shows alongside the final once the final itself is the active round. Earlier\nrounds still drop as each new round goes live.\n\nSplit via SportsWidgetMiddleware.noTeamMatches (threshold FULL_SCHEDULE_FROM_ROUND = QUARTER_FINAL); covered by SportsWidgetMiddlewareTest.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307340\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307650\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/home/sports/SportsWidgetMiddleware.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/test/java/org/mozilla/fenix/home/sports/SportsWidgetMiddlewareTest.kt"], "git_node": "0d6183173e426dc1119b598cba9aff9cecd303f5", "git_parents": ["56d057b2d0c72133c023c8e3a372d87bd523e45f"], "node": "2bf018e318e856ea5bf76fc4aee218c721894d10", "parents": ["b157c4bcc101a494b124a20de809e0e14a5b4129"], "tags": []}], "date": 1781856705, "git_changesets": ["0d6183173e426dc1119b598cba9aff9cecd303f5"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "26959": {"changesets": [{"author": "Release Engineering Landoscript \u003crelease+landoscript@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nach -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\naf -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nan -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nar -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nast -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\naz -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nbe -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nbg -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nbn -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nbr -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nbs -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nca -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nca-valencia -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\ncak -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\ncs -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\ncy -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nda -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nde -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\ndsb -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nel -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nen-CA -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nen-GB -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\neo -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nes-AR -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nes-CL -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nes-ES -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f67e85243273a9\nes-MX -\u003e ef803571d61c8404f89e97edd4f