: "tags-unified", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 31810c073a58f33a7804a10fc23a78cbe5ca78be with FIREFOX-ANDROID_152_0_2_RELEASE a=tagging CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": "8776ce4ffec253c088b4036baba62598798a91c3", "git_parents": ["2df5b5bd1164fb1eb6eb5d1bd0af43becbf80892"], "node": "b923265375a21124c3bbd9f9b20e53e08a5adfe6", "parents": ["aeb2ca37f02b89aab3d172b3452e31dcfe9dfcf3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782221036, "git_changesets": ["8776ce4ffec253c088b4036baba62598798a91c3"], "user": "ffxbld@lando.moz.tools"}, "27031": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045604 - Don't leak the static doc via the relevant global of the context.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D306772\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307725\n", "files": ["dom/canvas/nsICanvasRenderingContextInternal.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLCanvasElement.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLCanvasElement.h"], "git_node": "060ef86e4d8a87d8395d0a651b70604c731e1143", "git_parents": ["24787d164aaad0497ce6325a2c8d1c003707dbe6"], "node": "cc9c63c56a507a6b5e76744488e13c9d4d6120f2", "parents": ["d39831f6c91bd276425ad3b5f841180d25868bac"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782221574, "git_changesets": ["060ef86e4d8a87d8395d0a651b70604c731e1143"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27032": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045406 - Validate end of cff dict.  a=pascalc\n\nSent upstream in https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/cairo/cairo/-/work_items/967\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305850\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307730\n", "files": ["gfx/cairo/cairo/src/cairo-cff-subset.c", "gfx/cairo/patches/0034-cff-dict-validation.patch"], "git_node": "9956665b1c2bbe49740b990ccaf9e801f0c9a92d", "git_parents": ["060ef86e4d8a87d8395d0a651b70604c731e1143"], "node": "dfbadc90ac1a7dd72ae5b5586c899e7207635a56", "parents": ["cc9c63c56a507a6b5e76744488e13c9d4d6120f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045406 - Check cff dict operator / operand sizes.  a=pascalc\n\nMissed this one from the AI report. Also submitted upstream.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D306885\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307731\n", "files": ["gfx/cairo/cairo/src/cairo-cff-subset.c", "gfx/cairo/patches/0036-cff-operator-bounds.patch"], "git_node": "38515c84d9f86372c392bd90450e0e894b18d8d5", "git_parents": ["9956665b1c2bbe49740b990ccaf9e801f0c9a92d"], "node": "07fac135186c823c72dfc0b97e91919a2e96f2c3", "parents": ["dfbadc90ac1a7dd72ae5b5586c899e7207635a56"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782221672, "git_changesets": ["9956665b1c2bbe49740b990ccaf9e801f0c9a92d", "38515c84d9f86372c392bd90450e0e894b18d8d5"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27033": {"changesets": [{"author": "David Shin \u003cdshin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045181:  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307283\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307765\n", "files": ["layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.cpp"], "git_node": "00973d7a3d13d561656796062bb37d9fccb887f4", "git_parents": ["38515c84d9f86372c392bd90450e0e894b18d8d5"], "node": "4745537cbb0e1898b1738e68eca9d06a093da605", "parents": ["07fac135186c823c72dfc0b97e91919a2e96f2c3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782222419, "git_changesets": ["00973d7a3d13d561656796062bb37d9fccb887f4"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27034": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045451 - Prevent allocation of object elemets abutting the end of a nursery chunk  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305804\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307779\n", "files": ["js/src/gc/Nursery.cpp"], "git_node": "1277773c828b05d4ffbf7ba441d29442d42e76a8", "git_parents": ["00973d7a3d13d561656796062bb37d9fccb887f4"], "node": "c523ac187bd1bccf0d796589e203eefc55c26bd3", "parents": ["4745537cbb0e1898b1738e68eca9d06a093da605"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782222476, "git_changesets": ["1277773c828b05d4ffbf7ba441d29442d42e76a8"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27035": {"changesets": [{"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe.birchill@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2039987 - Encapsulate CompositorBridgeParent's indirect layer tree map; forbid operator[].  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nMake sIndirectLayerTrees and sIndirectLayerTreesLock private, and give\nLayerTreeMap a deleted operator[]. std::map::operator[] silently inserts a\ndefault (null) entry on a missing key, and using it to read or mutate an\nalready-erased layer tree during shutdown resurrects a bogus entry; deleting it\nturns every such site into a compile error so lookup vs insertion is always\nexplicit.\n\nAll access now goes through:\n  WithIndirectLayerTreesLock(fn)  - the only way to take the lock; passes a proof\n  GetLayerTreeStateUnderLock      - non-inserting lookup (nullptr if absent)\n  EnsureLayerTreeStateUnderLock   - explicit insert-or-get (try_emplace)\n  EraseLayerTreeStateUnderLock    - erase if present\n  ForEachLayerTreeStateUnderLock  - iterate\n  CallWithLayerTreeState          - mutate the entry if present (self-locking)\n\nThis is a behavior-preserving refactor: every former operator[] becomes an\nexplicit insert-or-get (EnsureLayerTreeStateUnderLock / try_emplace).\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307511\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307985\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/APZInputBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/ContentCompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/ContentCompositorBridgeParent.h"], "git_node": "8c44f815c98812f5ac0cbf5c2365d14236d1c93e", "git_parents": ["1277773c828b05d4ffbf7ba441d29442d42e76a8"], "node": "7ab380ea49407e1333db16f830560849b2a7dc1c", "parents": ["c523ac187bd1bccf0d796589e203eefc55c26bd3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe.birchill@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2039987 - Don't resurrect an erased layer tree state when clearing mWebRenderAPI on shutdown.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nDuring compositor shutdown, CompositorBridgeParent::StopAndClearResources()\nnulled sIndirectLayerTrees[mRootLayerTreeID].mWebRenderAPI. By that point the\nentry for mRootLayerTreeID may already have been erased (e.g. on the headless\nmacOS aarch64 VM workers after a GPU device reset), so the (former) operator[]\nre-inserted it with a null mApzcTreeManagerParent. When the APZCTreeManagerParent\nfor that root was then torn down, DisconnectApzcTreeManager found the resurrected\nnull-slot entry and tripped MOZ_ASSERT(state.mApzcTreeManagerParent ==\naTreeManager).\n\nUse CallWithLayerTreeState, which only runs when the entry is present, so an\nalready-erased root layer tree stays erased and the disconnect takes its clean\nnot-found early return.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307512\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307986\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": "c0dffcb04ab4d5b932dc1f460120859992d41532", "git_parents": ["8c44f815c98812f5ac0cbf5c2365d14236d1c93e"], "node": "44bb7b44552648c24ce8c84ddbb66daae020e52c", "parents": ["7ab380ea49407e1333db16f830560849b2a7dc1c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782222589, "git_changesets": ["8c44f815c98812f5ac0cbf5c2365d14236d1c93e", "c0dffcb04ab4d5b932dc1f460120859992d41532"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27036": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2046928 - Re-check AllowNewWrapper for the WindowProxy.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307475\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307996\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/realms/bug2046928.js", "js/src/vm/Compartment.cpp"], "git_node": "22157a5c06ee4d1163579f48a4ae0508f2fc4bbe", "git_parents": ["c0dffcb04ab4d5b932dc1f460120859992d41532"], "node": "0e23b190d43fa36aea376c37b80d3ade9fc5e4e3", "parents": ["44bb7b44552648c24ce8c84ddbb66daae020e52c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782222719, "git_changesets": ["22157a5c06ee4d1163579f48a4ae0508f2fc4bbe"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27037": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andreas Farre \u003cfarre@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045618 - Make sure to consider idle timeouts when getting id.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305582\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307999\n", "files": ["dom/base/TimeoutManager.cpp"], "git_node": "2346c5c9a04f82e12d1840fdfe80ad679f617d1b", "git_parents": ["22157a5c06ee4d1163579f48a4ae0508f2fc4bbe"], "node": "697ed9d225294846e848ea74a84d9a5acaa8f2a0", "parents": ["0e23b190d43fa36aea376c37b80d3ade9fc5e4e3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782222796, "git_changesets": ["2346c5c9a04f82e12d1840fdfe80ad679f617d1b"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27038": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gela \u003cgmalekpour@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032561 - Part 1: Collect telemetry using the existing metrics added for VPN  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\n**Scenario\u2019s tested and verified:**\n\nSet breakpoints on all the newly added record calls and ensure they get hit:\n1. When user goes to the VPN settings page from the \u2026 menu\n2. When user enables, disables or presses \u201cTry it\u201d on the \u2026 menu\n3. When user toggles the VPN on or off from the VPN settings screen\n4. When user clicks on Get Started in the VPN settings screen prior to authenticating or authorizing\n5. When user goes to the VPN settings page from the Settings fragment.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D306452\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308041\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/metrics.yaml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/browser/BaseBrowserFragment.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionInfoPrompter.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/components/menu/MenuDialogFragment.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/home/HomeFragment.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/settings/IPProtectionFragment.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/settings/SettingsFragment.kt"], "git_node": "6b9588313899cdba73f8b8327e836e4f18ee3c61", "git_parents": ["2346c5c9a04f82e12d1840fdfe80ad679f617d1b"], "node": "4942d5b04f41037c57ba91da6f234459b9b8cff2", "parents": ["697ed9d225294846e848ea74a84d9a5acaa8f2a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gela \u003cgmalekpour@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032561 - Part 2: Add telemetry for VPN in trust panel  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\n**Scenario\u2019s tested and verified:**\n\nSet breakpoints on all the newly added record calls and ensure they get hit:\n1. When user taps on \u201cTry it\u201d from the trust panel\n2. When VPN is toggled on or off from the trust panel\n3. When user goes to the VPN settings screen from the trust panel\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D306489\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308042\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/metrics.yaml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/settings/trustpanel/TrustPanelFragment.kt"], "git_node": "a983604bfa4ddb9354b5788a07c1e0ae5f2d53ac", "git_parents": ["6b9588313899cdba73f8b8327e836e4f18ee3c61"], "node": "2d678ebf6d7fddb675b8022eee326a054ff42252", "parents": ["4942d5b04f41037c57ba91da6f234459b9b8cff2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gela \u003cgmalekpour@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032561 - Part 3: Add VPN telemetry for authorization and authentication and record durations  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\n**Scenario\u2019s tested and verified:**\n\n**Recording Authentication:**\n1. Set a break point on the calls for recording metrics for authentication flow completed\n2. Open the Firefox browser while not signed in and go to the VPN settings screen and click on Get started\n3. In the custom tab enter a pre-existing VPN account credential and ensure the breakpoint on `fxAccountFlowCompleted` gets hit.\n4. Ensure that the reported duration number matches how long it took in real life.\n\n**Recording Authorization:**\n1. Set a break point on the calls for recording metrics for authorization flow completed\n2. Open the Firefox browser while signed in with an account that has not used or authorized the VPN before and go to the VPN settings screen and click on Get started\n3. In the custom tab enter the credentials for an account that has not used/authorized the VPN before and ensure the breakpoint on `fxAuthorizationFlowCompleted` gets hit.\n4. Ensure that the reported duration number matches how long it took in real life.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307169\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308043\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/components/ipprotection/IPProtection.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionTelemetryMiddleware.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/test/java/org/mozilla/fenix/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionTelemetryMiddlewareTest.kt"], "git_node": "c920849430da6fd147c22039a23ef8f25dd40f1b", "git_parents": ["a983604bfa4ddb9354b5788a07c1e0ae5f2d53ac"], "node": "43879c07169ef831934984e3249718b653ad0cf9", "parents": ["2d678ebf6d7fddb675b8022eee326a054ff42252"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782223041, "git_changesets": ["6b9588313899cdba73f8b8327e836e4f18ee3c61", "a983604bfa4ddb9354b5788a07c1e0ae5f2d53ac", "c920849430da6fd147c22039a23ef8f25dd40f1b"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27039": {"changesets": [{"author": "Diego Escalante \u003cdescalante@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045278 - Put farthest-corner and closest-corner parameters for ellipse() behind a nightly-only.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305186\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308053\n", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml", "servo/components/style/values/specified/basic_shape.rs", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/__dir__.ini"], "git_node": "928cfb89f409c28f83c9921c7f70941811a6a901", "git_parents": ["c920849430da6fd147c22039a23ef8f25dd40f1b"], "node": "51ab2a5d42d298baacc938502bed90e0d48e45bb", "parents": ["43879c07169ef831934984e3249718b653ad0cf9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782223098, "git_changesets": ["928cfb89f409c28f83c9921c7f70941811a6a901"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27040": {"changesets": [{"author": "Diego Escalante \u003cdescalante@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2048959 - Enable ellipse corner parsing and computation for layout mochitests.  a=pascalc DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307878\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308055\n", "files": ["layout/style/test/mochitest.toml"], "git_node": "391c9f9d63f0a77bd5264d1e0b7049aac6fcad4c", "git_parents": ["928cfb89f409c28f83c9921c7f70941811a6a901"], "node": "7831b703c7e2eaf41a21be71cd89b5c53460126e", "parents": ["51ab2a5d42d298baacc938502bed90e0d48e45bb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782223155, "git_chang