: make EncryptedBlock::RoundedUpToBasicBlockSize public and use it in EncryptingOutputStream, and propertly clear buffer  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309603\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309999\n", "files": ["dom/quota/EncryptedBlock.h", "dom/quota/EncryptingOutputStream_impl.h"], "git_node": "c97ff0c88fd36a75667c2f2c501ede6cf31a711f", "git_parents": ["8a2f9b6700b248b430ad3c6197d9ffe063fbf860"], "node": "8344208208ee59e44452b7260f6f839dbbf60a47", "parents": ["240feab86e847aa76cd59c36e664c9b81f43d391"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982412, "git_changesets": ["8a2f9b6700b248b430ad3c6197d9ffe063fbf860", "c97ff0c88fd36a75667c2f2c501ede6cf31a711f"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27222": {"changesets": [{"author": "Eden Chuang \u003cechuang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026301 - Synchronize ThreadSafeRequestHandle::mRunnable to fix cross-thread use-after-free  a=pascalc\n\nmRunnable was a plain RefPtr read on the main thread (GetCacheCreator and the\nother accessors) and cleared on the worker thread by ReleaseRequest() with no\nsynchronization. When the worker's store dropped the last reference to the\nshared ScriptLoaderRunnable, the main thread could dereference the already-freed\npointer, producing a heap-use-after-free.\n\nGuard mRunnable with a Mutex (enforced via MOZ_GUARDED_BY). ReleaseRequest() and\nthe new SetRunnable() mutate it under the lock, releasing the runnable outside\nthe lock so it is never destroyed while the mutex is held. Each main-thread\naccessor copies mRunnable into a local strong reference under the lock and bails\nif it was already released. GetCacheCreator() now returns a strong CacheCreator\nreference taken under the lock, so the caller keeps it alive across DeleteCache()\neven if the runnable is released on the worker thread afterwards.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307211\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309997\n", "files": ["dom/workers/ScriptLoader.cpp", "dom/workers/loader/CacheLoadHandler.cpp", "dom/workers/loader/NetworkLoadHandler.cpp", "dom/workers/loader/WorkerLoadContext.cpp", "dom/workers/loader/WorkerLoadContext.h"], "git_node": "4cd1770650007d0528eac8097ee766d235d7edd7", "git_parents": ["c97ff0c88fd36a75667c2f2c501ede6cf31a711f"], "node": "0e2afa7b0aafb4f0ec9b0353330ed492fcadacd2", "parents": ["8344208208ee59e44452b7260f6f839dbbf60a47"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982501, "git_changesets": ["4cd1770650007d0528eac8097ee766d235d7edd7"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27223": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2051666.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309674\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309981\n", "files": ["gfx/2d/ScaledFontDWrite.cpp"], "git_node": "424d78d3a915b5147132816483a1441ee2c4a4b1", "git_parents": ["4cd1770650007d0528eac8097ee766d235d7edd7"], "node": "d8834432bea131deb1e160bacda8479b9890cf41", "parents": ["0e2afa7b0aafb4f0ec9b0353330ed492fcadacd2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982584, "git_changesets": ["424d78d3a915b5147132816483a1441ee2c4a4b1"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27224": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2049405.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308437\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309965\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h"], "git_node": "d3feb3c60cda5418172aef78b6941729e793677c", "git_parents": ["424d78d3a915b5147132816483a1441ee2c4a4b1"], "node": "cf381297d99ca89c51d25d2f37b5637607e1b4a4", "parents": ["d8834432bea131deb1e160bacda8479b9890cf41"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982636, "git_changesets": ["d3feb3c60cda5418172aef78b6941729e793677c"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27225": {"changesets": [{"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050627: Ensure the correct acc type for a RemoteAccessible.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308963\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309958\n", "files": ["accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.cpp", "accessible/windows/uia/uiaRawElmProvider.cpp", "accessible/windows/uia/uiaRawElmProvider.h"], "git_node": "3f577ff19d57b225ea3d68a53b05eed2afd24e80", "git_parents": ["d3feb3c60cda5418172aef78b6941729e793677c"], "node": "98d72af369d911c52a46be683bc5111c4f4076f9", "parents": ["cf381297d99ca89c51d25d2f37b5637607e1b4a4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982778, "git_changesets": ["3f577ff19d57b225ea3d68a53b05eed2afd24e80"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27226": {"changesets": [{"author": "Chun-Min Chang \u003cchun.m.chang@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2047723 - Cherry-pick commit f738b1132ec1fd56efc90367898244cf52d9e6a5 for libsoundtouch  a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309943\n", "files": ["media/libsoundtouch/moz.yaml", "media/libsoundtouch/ratetransposer-clamp-dest-size.patch", "media/libsoundtouch/src/RateTransposer.cpp"], "git_node": "f05b775ef3084be96a808cea5c790b2c7d7d0a34", "git_parents": ["3f577ff19d57b225ea3d68a53b05eed2afd24e80"], "node": "cc88bf5b9d7c55e94c2c0c60fbdd7aa30e163786", "parents": ["98d72af369d911c52a46be683bc5111c4f4076f9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982883, "git_changesets": ["f05b775ef3084be96a808cea5c790b2c7d7d0a34"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27227": {"changesets": [{"author": "David Rubino \u003cdrubino@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050775 - Defer Windows launch-on-login first-run enablement to browser-idle-startup.  a=pascalc\n\nThe first-run launch-on-login entry point ran in the browser-before-ui-startup\ncategory, where it awaited Nimbus's first Remote Settings fetch. Forcing Remote\nSettings initialization on the pre-UI critical path did significant disk I/O and\nregressed Talos startup file-I/O metrics (tp5n main_startup_fileio and friends),\nts_paint, and sessionrestore on Windows.\n\nThe Windows startup-apps registry key only needs to be written before the user\nreboots, so this work has ample slack. Move the registration to the\nbrowser-idle-startup category so it is dispatched once the browser is idle,\nkeeping the Nimbus/Remote Settings I/O off the startup measurement window. The\nfeature behavior is unchanged.\n\nAlso update the registration test to expect the browser-idle-startup category.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309204\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309940\n", "files": ["browser/components/BrowserComponents.manifest", "browser/components/defaultwindowslaunchonlogin/tests/test_DefaultWindowsLaunchOnLogin.js"], "git_node": "c7cc31441d1abf1810f387380451ef5014ff69f1", "git_parents": ["f05b775ef3084be96a808cea5c790b2c7d7d0a34"], "node": "0266bfbc192ad7bde67fb8a8e613ccfbeafd7fe4", "parents": ["cc88bf5b9d7c55e94c2c0c60fbdd7aa30e163786"], "tags": []}], "date": 1782982967, "git_changesets": ["c7cc31441d1abf1810f387380451ef5014ff69f1"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27228": {"changesets": [{"author": "Release Engineering Landoscript \u003crelease+landoscript@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nach -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\naf -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\nan -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\nar -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\nast -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\naz -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\nbe -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\nbg -\u003e 4e0cffd8a0142da51c76eb205097f4961aa828d5\nbn -\u