n initialization failure  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308458\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310566\n", "files": ["js/src/builtin/ModuleObject.cpp", "js/src/builtin/ModuleObject.h", "js/src/vm/Modules.cpp"], "git_node": "dd27dc2b11bf735054427cca9a828e6a09e49dc1", "git_parents": ["ce04d58ed7695c55b4b2ce7e5d8a58560369cc90"], "node": "d1b539f73c8f12697e7f116285161ee4a202900f", "parents": ["1ece927921e11a25995a567ef326d2256e1fd09e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361455, "git_changesets": ["dd27dc2b11bf735054427cca9a828e6a09e49dc1"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27321": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2046916 - Simplify background alloc heuristic  a=pascalc\n\nWe don't need to iterate over all zones here to check whether the heap is\nsmall. We can check the heap size instead. These checks aren't exactly\nequivalent but this is only a rough heuristic anyway.\n\nI couldn't get the test case to reproduce so it's not included. The patch\navoids the possibility of racing by removing the offending code.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307220\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310567\n", "files": ["js/src/gc/Allocator.cpp", "js/src/gc/GC.cpp", "js/src/gc/PublicIterators.h"], "git_node": "146ccbd885529ca6442e5c97ee9e1e179a973f05", "git_parents": ["dd27dc2b11bf735054427cca9a828e6a09e49dc1"], "node": "6edcdf0034923893897288381032f13e276eb0a1", "parents": ["d1b539f73c8f12697e7f116285161ee4a202900f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361505, "git_changesets": ["146ccbd885529ca6442e5c97ee9e1e179a973f05"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27322": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2046917 - Make implicit edge marking state runtime wide  a=pascalc\n\nCurrently this is tracked per-marker but the effect should be per-runtime.\nThere may be multiple markers due to parallel marking.\n\nI couldn't get the tescase to reproduce here either.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307221\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310569\n", "files": ["js/src/gc/GC.cpp", "js/src/gc/GCMarker.h", "js/src/gc/GCRuntime.h", "js/src/gc/Marking.cpp", "js/src/gc/Verifier.cpp"], "git_node": "f8daaf187420f9b15a7727cebdea0dcf8c4790fa", "git_parents": ["146ccbd885529ca6442e5c97ee9e1e179a973f05"], "node": "d8ab1038d9824edcf3631805060660c2f7cfac98", "parents": ["6edcdf0034923893897288381032f13e276eb0a1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361575, "git_changesets": ["f8daaf187420f9b15a7727cebdea0dcf8c4790fa"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27323": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2049418 - Take account of interaction between sweeping and the store buffer when updating weak ref targets  a=pascalc\n\nThe problem is that the weak ref we are updating is weakly held and may later\nbe found to be dead and swept. The post barrier triggered on the update can add\na pointer to the weak ref to the nursery store buffer, which can result in UAF\nif we don't clear out the nursery before we sweep the object.\n\nThe fix is to make use of the existing flag that is used to handle this\nsituation.\n\nI removed the previous incomplete fix for reasons of simplicitly.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308546\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310571\n", "files": ["js/src/gc/FinalizationObservers.cpp", "js/src/gc/GCRuntime.h", "js/src/jsapi.cpp"], "git_node": "8e3d3b3f1ad160606be439ad1055abf2b8bf2205", "git_parents": ["f8daaf187420f9b15a7727cebdea0dcf8c4790fa"], "node": "9157f7bc29b1e950e6a91ff0ca27b4f7cda66ff3", "parents": ["d8ab1038d9824edcf3631805060660c2f7cfac98"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361623, "git_changesets": ["8e3d3b3f1ad160606be439ad1055abf2b8bf2205"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27324": {"changesets": [{"author": "smayya \u003csmayya@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045511 - update nsHttpTransaction::Close() handling of NS_BINDING_RETARGETED.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307751\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310584\n", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpTransaction.cpp"], "git_node": "1b73ddeb50ecc611def0a0202df6df43374b5c2e", "git_parents": ["8e3d3b3f1ad160606be439ad1055abf2b8bf2205"], "node": "0df0439d607018779326005f52e7afadfe1e55c5", "parents": ["9157f7bc29b1e950e6a91ff0ca27b4f7cda66ff3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361661, "git_changesets": ["1b73ddeb50ecc611def0a0202df6df43374b5c2e"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27325": {"changesets": [{"author": "Manuel Bucher \u003cmanuel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2030652 - Await l10n translation before setting alert role on infobar notifications  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304830\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310596\n", "files": ["accessible/tests/browser/events/browser.toml", "accessible/tests/browser/events/browser_notification_infobar.js", "toolkit/content/widgets/notificationbox.js"], "git_node": "39c37f6c5c44b8831cfefaa5121ed0ef58e90a17", "git_parents": ["1b73ddeb50ecc611def0a0202df6df43374b5c2e"], "node": "ed8801aa129b19db60c0db434365612c55b7550e", "parents": ["0df0439d607018779326005f52e7afadfe1e55c5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361701, "git_changesets": ["39c37f6c5c44b8831cfefaa5121ed0ef58e90a17"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27326": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Seward \u003cjseward@acm.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2042739.  .  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307272\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310597\n", "files": ["js/src/jit/Ion.cpp"], "git_node": "9bbbabde3bb11603affea92f116e40ec73b05e31", "git_parents": ["39c37f6c5c44b8831cfefaa5121ed0ef58e90a17"], "node": "28639d99951db26d74fdc1be791fe0ad0a65f3c5", "parents": ["ed8801aa129b19db60c0db434365612c55b7550e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361739, "git_changesets": ["9bbbabde3bb11603affea92f116e40ec73b05e31"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27327": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2052703.  a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310598\n", "files": ["image/decoders/nsJXLDecoder.cpp"], "git_node": "3086965daacfdc5f1686ec058a7354fe3b919f18", "git_parents": ["9bbbabde3bb11603affea92f116e40ec73b05e31"], "node": "6ce54309016784645d32a3036ddbbd2d12118886", "parents": ["28639d99951db26d74fdc1be791fe0ad0a65f3c5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361807, "git_changesets": ["3086965daacfdc5f1686ec058a7354fe3b919f18"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27328": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gela \u003cgmalekpour@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050986 - Remove Scope Session  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310079\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310631\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/ipprotection/src/main/java/mozilla/components/feature/ipprotection/IPProtectionFxaAuthFlow.kt"], "git_node": "19bd4ee778b2762ad8c5bf227935742b8e1c9b87", "git_parents": ["3086965daacfdc5f1686ec058a7354fe3b919f18"], "node": "cc00f16c993d30227f5de75e84a06eb62f6baa30", "parents": ["6ce54309016784645d32a3036ddbbd2d12118886"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361847, "git_changesets": ["19bd4ee778b2762ad8c5bf227935742b8e1c9b87"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27329": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2047962 - Unwrap legacy data:text/plain, pref values in autoconfig.  ,Gijs  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309831\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310632\n", "files": ["extensions/pref/autoconfig/src/prefcalls.js", "extensions/pref/autoconfig/test/unit/autoconfig-all.cfg", "extensions/pref/autoconfig/test/unit/test_autoconfig.js"], "git_node": "bbf5dc543db8e7980608ddd32837a36efec7fa44", "git_parents": ["19bd4ee778b2762ad8c5bf227935742b8e1c9b87"], "node": "29779bb8d22c669e3ead1f31928b5420e38e983c", "parents": ["cc00f16c993d30227f5de75e84a06eb62f6baa30"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361884, "git_changesets": ["bbf5dc543db8e7980608ddd32837a36efec7fa44"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27330": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jonathan Almeida \u003cjonalmeida942@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050967 - Part 1: Add AccountScopeAccessor to read AccountStorage persisted state  a=pascalc\n\nWe introduce an accessor for reading our persisted account on disk by\nconsuming the JSON string first. This avoids having to know which\nSharedPreference type is used (secure or regular).\n\nThe accessor acts as a weak implementation wrapper to a future API that\nfeeds in from the native fxa_client.\n\nWe always read the state from disk for every request to ensure\nfreshness. This uses a background Corountine context to avoid IO on\nthe FxaAccountManager that does not need to be synchronized with it's\nown coroutineContext: this is a read-only check and reading may fail for\na variety of reasons, we do not need to block the account manager to\navoid these failures.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309749\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310650\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/service/firefox-accounts/build.gradle", "mobile/android/android-components/components/service/firefox-accounts/src/main/java/mozilla/components/service/fxa/manager/AccountScopeAccessor.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/service/firefox-accounts/src/main/java/mozilla/components/service/fxa/manager/FxaAccountManager.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/service/firefox-accounts/src/test/java/mozilla/components/service/fxa/FxaAccountManagerTest.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/service/firefox-accounts/src/test/java/mozilla/components/service/fxa/manager/AccountScopeAccessorTest.kt"], "git_node": "2f1c5b02f2cc511d1c41ff9ca0d446e5766e39db", "git_parents": ["bbf5dc543db8e7980608ddd32837a36efec7fa44"], "node": "7b6817306fb83db2eb6bdca9216a665a1283d002", "parents": ["29779bb8d22c669e3ead1f31928b5420e38e983c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Almeida \u003cjonalmeida942@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050967 - Part 2: Introduce account scope check to IPProtection  a=pascalc\n\nTo avoid DDOS-ing our servers, we check our existing scopes to see if we\ncan fetch an access token. If we don't have one and we are\nauthenticated, we try to perform a token exchange if our\naccount does have the global scope.\n\nThis is similar to behaviour from before, except that we only attempt\nthe token exchange when we enter the VPN UI screen. If the account was\nnot entitled, we then perform an authorization as we previously did.\n\nCo-authored-by: Mark Hammond \u003cmhammond@skippinet.com.au\u003e\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309985\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310651\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/ipprotection/src/main/java/mozilla/components/feature/ipprotection/IPProtectionStorageSynchronizer.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/ipprotection/src/main/java/mozilla/components/feature/ipprotection/store/Actions.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/ipprotection/src/main/java/mozilla/components/feature/ipprotection/store/Reducers.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/ipprotection/src/test/java/mozilla/components/feature/ipprotection/IPProtectionReducerTest.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/settings/IPProtectionFragment.kt"], "git_node": "ba5372c91e65d4f02f8f600ff4a0f5a9ac11fbc2", "git_parents": ["2f1c5b02f2cc511d1c41ff9ca0d446e5766e39db"], "node": "34c2fde2bd41beceb88bbe33341ad809a9106cdd", "parents": ["7b6817306fb83db2eb6bdca9216a665a1283d002"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783361958, "git_changesets": ["2f1c5b02f2cc511d1c41ff9ca0d446e5766e39db", "ba5372c91e65d4f02f8f600ff4a0f5a9ac11fbc2"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27331": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mathew Hodson \u003cmathew.hodson@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2035442 - Update whatCanYouDoItems for dnsNotFound error  a=pascalc\n\nThe `dnsNotFound` error's customNetError config previously used a single `whatCanYouDoL10nId` pointing to a generic offline message. This patch replaces it with an array of three `l10n` ids that more accurately reflect what a user can do when DNS resolution fails: a general network hint, a check-network hint, and a firewall hint. I also added a test to check that the correct items are configured.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D300941\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310204\n", "files": ["toolkit/content/errors/net-errors.mjs", "toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_error_registry.js", "toolkit/locales/en-US/toolkit/neterror/netError.ftl"], "git_node": "457fb049b801367b6e399d83243b442a8d6cbc12", "git_parents": ["ba5372c91e65d4f02f8f600ff4a0f5a9ac11fbc2"], "node": "39330a19f24028e5eb9d53455f75e4e7efccf23f", "parents": ["34c2fde2bd41beceb88bbe33341ad809a9106cdd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783365110, "git_changesets": ["457fb049b801367b6e399d83243b442a8d6cbc12"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27332": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP -  a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310423\n", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": "0859f53e99664690d1c8e2f09c4c8a27d09b49a9", "git_parents": ["457fb049b801367b6e399d83243b442a8d6cbc12"], "node": "c56cd6a41f4924fcd4392b4f73e1a5390593a712", "parents": ["39330a19f24028e5eb9d53455f75e4e7efccf23f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783368093, "git_changesets": ["0859f53e99664690d1c8e2f09c4c8a27d09b49a9"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27333": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rolf Rando \u003crrando@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2048511 - Failsafe and chunk size adjustments to support slower embedding models in the future  a=pascalc\n\nSemantic search of history creates embeddings in groups (chunks) from the title and description in the user's history.\n\nCurrently in Nightly p95 Semantic Search history back-fill chunk generation time is 326 ms with Onnx-native, 846ml with Onnx wasm. p50 times are significantly lower (~20 ms).\n\nWe have several mitigations in place for slow machines.\n\n- If we see we're slow  (\u003e300ms, configurable) generating the chunks, we cut the items per chunk in half (with minimum 10), then wait until the next places event until resume -- these events happen often when users are actively browsing. One exception is that if we're \u003c 1000 entries don't take any of these mitigations, as we want to quickly build a cache.\n\n- If we see we're extremely slow (\u003e500ms chunk times) we stop generating altogether and block regenerating chunks until browser restart.\n\nWe have a lower bar for activating semantic search for users during queries. Now it's just 10 entries\n\nEverything is reset on restart of places engine (presumably browser restart).\n\nAlso, we're trying to avoid slower onnx-wasm engines by reverting to static embeddings on linux. If a user copied their profile between machines from Linux to a Mac, the embeddings would restart. Onnx-wasm will work if needed and benefits from optimizations above. Likely we will target non-linux users in the first pass of testing.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307476\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310665\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ml/content/nlp/EmbeddingsGenerator.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ml/tests/browser/browser_ml_embeddings_generator.js", "toolkit/components/nimbus/FeatureManifest.yaml", "toolkit/components/places/PlacesSemanticHistoryManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/places/metrics.yaml", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unit/test_PlacesSemanticHistoryManager.js", "tools/@types/generated/lib.gecko.glean.d.ts"], "git_node": "89d956be05ddd2fddfd46763afc4609bb72f5241", "git_parents": ["0859f53e99664690d1c8e2f09c4c8a27d09b49a9"], "node": "b207792f8b7b512f3e7dce2aa096e535f4930fa7", "parents": ["c56cd6a41f4924fcd4392b4f73e1a5390593a712"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783368939, "git_changesets": ["89d956be05ddd2fddfd46763afc4609bb72f5241"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27334": {"changesets": [{"author": "Release Engineering Landoscript \u003crelease+landoscript@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug - Import translations from main\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/media/src/main/res/values-fi/strings.xml", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/prompts/src/main/res/values-fi/strings.xml", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/protection-dashboard/src/main/res/values-fi/strings.xml", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/summarize/src/main/res/values-fi/strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values-cs/strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values-fi/strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values-pa-rIN/strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values-tg/strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values-tr/strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values-vi/strings.xml"], "git_node": "ebc989f4fac11d7ee4c88a4c470615501e2a0ae2", "git_parents": ["89d956be05ddd2fddfd46763afc4609bb72f5241"], "node": "f9ccb92516917beeda53950095ef738cfcb3b26f", "parents": ["b207792f8b7b512f3e7dce2aa096e535f4930fa7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783390623, "git_changesets": ["ebc989f4fac11d7ee4c88a4c470615501e2a0ae2"], "user": "ffxbld@lando.moz.tools"}, "27335": {"changesets": [{"author": "Release Engineering Landoscript \u003crelease+landoscript@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nach -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\naf -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nan -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nar -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nast -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\naz -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nbe -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nbg -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nbn -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nbr -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nbs -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nca -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nca-valencia -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\ncak -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\ncs -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\ncy -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nda -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nde -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\ndsb -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nel -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nen-CA -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nen-GB -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\neo -\u003e 82eddc22402bf691772703e4637fc7c9e3faf1e5\nes-AR -\u003e 82eddc22