Smart Cursor actions in Smart Window behind `browser.ml.chat.shortcuts.smartwindow` and route selected text to the sidebar chat\n- Update Smart Window context menus/shortcuts to use Smart Window-specific UI and remove unsupported options\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D306022\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311426\n", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/DesktopActorRegistry.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/metrics.yaml", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/components/ai-window/ai-window.mjs", "browser/components/genai/GenAI.sys.mjs", "browser/components/genai/tests/browser/browser_chat_contextmenu.js", "browser/components/genai/tests/browser/browser_chat_shortcuts.js", "browser/components/genai/tests/browser/browser_genai_actors.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/genai.ftl"], "git_node": "e0a9de161997105e9c1f349ab910bf8992bef95c", "git_parents": ["b4f8c51c72ca60cb7141e368b4b4555b674fa14c"], "node": "41875423fedb2706df165a406f2fdef3f896ae40", "parents": ["28b41fca37e2ea96135c7bcbd95d6ec206c48f27"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Elissa Cha \u003cecha@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2044112 - smart cursor for smart window: usage telemetry, setting to disable, default enable  a=RyanVM\n\n- Flip `browser.ml.chat.shortcuts.smartwindow` default to true so smart cursor shows in Smart Window by default\n- Add a setting in `about:preferences#personalizeSmartWindow` backed by above pref\n- Add `smart_window boolean` to `promptClick` telemetry\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309646\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311538\n", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/genai/GenAI.sys.mjs", "browser/components/genai/metrics.yaml", "browser/components/genai/tests/browser/browser_chat_contextmenu.js", "browser/components/genai/tests/browser/browser_chat_shortcuts.js", "browser/components/genai/tests/browser/browser_chat_telemetry.js", "browser/components/preferences/config/aiFeatures.mjs", "browser/locales-preview/aiFeatures.ftl"], "git_node": "eab31a851cf6d66b6b252cdd4cae80f5a041d4c1", "git_parents": ["e0a9de161997105e9c1f349ab910bf8992bef95c"], "node": "a843ec697aaa3486bc13f2ab9642a9b81f598c36", "parents": ["41875423fedb2706df165a406f2fdef3f896ae40"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783882962, "git_changesets": ["e0a9de161997105e9c1f349ab910bf8992bef95c", "eab31a851cf6d66b6b252cdd4cae80f5a041d4c1"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "27407": {"changesets": [{"author": "Moritz Beier \u003cmbeier@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2053049 - Call querySelector in UrlbarSearchOneOffs on input instead of panel.  a=RyanVM\n\nThis way, it works even before UrlbarInput::#populateSlots runs.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311096\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311480\n", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarSearchOneOffs.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "57e770b6c217fc4696c3a4970be41c968459da0c", "git_parents": ["eab31a851cf6d66b6b252cdd4cae80f5a041d4c1"], "node": "08848afaa40f34645172becdf2495011bf6dc89c", "parents": ["a843ec697aaa3486bc13f2ab9642a9b81f598c36"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783882995, "git_changesets": ["57e770b6c217fc4696c3a4970be41c968459da0c"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "27408": {"changesets": [{"author": "Stephen A Pohl \u003cspohl@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2053177: Defer the macOS file picker callback until the modal has unwound.  a=RyanVM\n\nOn macOS 26, the NSSavePanel/NSOpenPanel sheet completion handler can run before the panel's modal session has fully unwound. We invoke nsIFilePickerShownCallback::Done() synchronously from inside that completion handler, so a consumer that opens another modal from Done() (for example Thunderbird's \"Backup Secret Key to File\" flow in bug 2052844) starts the new modal on top of a session that is still tearing down, which hangs.\n\nDefer Done() to a fresh main-thread turn in all four picker modes (open, open-multiple, folder, save) so the modal finishes unwinding first. This matches the JS-side workaround of bouncing off Services.tm.dispatchToMainThread before launching the next modal, but fixes it once for every file-picker consumer. The callback still runs on the main thread exactly once with the same ResultCode; only its timing moves one turn later.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310869\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311500\n", "files": ["widget/cocoa/nsFilePicker.mm"], "git_node": "f845294820b260702527fcabb556bc01a4e4f3be", "git_parents": ["57e770b6c217fc4696c3a4970be41c968459da0c"], "node": "a2943824ee6137e77c0fe10c6e2fa18544c54f62", "parents": ["08848afaa40f34645172becdf2495011bf6dc89c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783883054, "git_changesets": ["f845294820b260702527fcabb556bc01a4e4f3be"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "27409": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Schuster \u003ctschuster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050430.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309544\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310291\n", "files": ["dom/bindings/BindingUtils.cpp", "dom/reporting/ReportingUtils.cpp", "dom/reporting/ReportingUtils.h", "dom/reporting/tests/common_deprecated.js", "dom/security/featurepolicy/FeaturePolicyUtils.cpp"], "git_node": "4bb555efc73c8666eb0e3e424396c0f6afde3eb0", "git_parents": ["f845294820b260702527fcabb556bc01a4e4f3be"], "node": "9c11ed655138eeb02cdb860f4a53e8a088796ea5", "parents": ["a2943824ee6137e77c0fe10c6e2fa18544c54f62"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783886209, "git_changesets": ["4bb555efc73c8666eb0e3e424396c0f6afde3eb0"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "27410": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045407 - Validate surface format properly.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305381\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310849\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/DcompSurfaceImage.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/d3d11/TextureD3D11.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/DMABUFTextureHostOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/MacIOSurfaceTextureHostOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/TextureHostOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/AsyncImagePipelineManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderMessageUtils.h", "gfx/webrender_bindings/WebRenderTypes.h", "image/BlobSurfaceProvider.cpp", "layout/generic/TextDrawTarget.h"], "git_node": "56d362936f4c403a3e11400e7d44892ee6175a0c", "git_parents": ["4bb555efc73c8666eb0e3e424396c0f6afde3eb0"], "node": "43ba9d6f9f94a2e9bdc2bfcc0ac304687b7ab2c4", "parents": ["9c11ed655138eeb02cdb860f4a53e8a088796ea5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783886367, "git_changesets": ["56d362936f4c403a3e11400e7d44892ee6175a0c"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "27411": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update remote-settings ct-logs -  a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311729\n", "files": ["security/ct/CTKnownLogs.h", "security/manager/tools/log_list.json", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons-bloomfilters.json", "services/settings/dumps/security-state/intermediates.json"], "git_node": "8a7579316884f0cccf2a9ce49c9c7b6a4efacd5a", "git_parents": ["56d362936f4c403a3e11400e7d44892ee6175a0c"], "node": "c6c7a34f825691c4071d87b373415d896045bcf4", "parents": ["43ba9d6f9f94a2e9bdc2bfcc0ac304687b7ab2c4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783889430, "git_changesets": ["8a7579316884f0cccf2a9ce49c9c7b6a4efacd5a"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "27412": {"changesets": [{"autho