ScrollState.maxValue\ninstead of a one-shot launch in onSizeChanged.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308501\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311556\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/compose/browser-toolbar/src/main/java/mozilla/components/compose/browser/toolbar/ui/HighlightedDomainUrl.kt"], "git_node": "02a9d0864c62052197cdbc35eae24169adf6e2f6", "git_parents": ["0158c032ced08cff80dce33360f158d180c468c5"], "node": "ea00003c84961b8e28f2b513f37c1e6b5ea5936a", "parents": ["ce413a7cb2aef8b6da95b4ea686d34e2997f69ef"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783929353, "git_changesets": ["02a9d0864c62052197cdbc35eae24169adf6e2f6"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27424": {"changesets": [{"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2045848: Avoid avoid re-initting usrsctp  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309814\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311555\n", "files": ["netwerk/sctp/datachannel/DataChannelUsrsctp.cpp"], "git_node": "4e2e35b31d3f7dc077766b30cef1e9cdd9206935", "git_parents": ["02a9d0864c62052197cdbc35eae24169adf6e2f6"], "node": "90387883ac9013a3b6397ee1f6034aaba3b7786b", "parents": ["ea00003c84961b8e28f2b513f37c1e6b5ea5936a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783929432, "git_changesets": ["4e2e35b31d3f7dc077766b30cef1e9cdd9206935"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27425": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2053375 - Enable html color picker for WPT.  a=pascalc\n\nWe can't close the native color picker on navigation so it gets reported\nas a leak...\n\nSee bug 1860336 comment 97 and onward.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311005\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311528\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/__dir__.ini"], "git_node": "4f5d31103ac192fbbc4ff6659a77d56bdb619dda", "git_parents": ["4e2e35b31d3f7dc077766b30cef1e9cdd9206935"], "node": "d5ee300bd8c20e62b0280c2c531313fa8f68f04b", "parents": ["90387883ac9013a3b6397ee1f6034aaba3b7786b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930102, "git_changesets": ["4f5d31103ac192fbbc4ff6659a77d56bdb619dda"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27426": {"changesets": [{"author": "smayya \u003csmayya@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033733 - enable LNA for all desktop users by default.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311474\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311519\n", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml"], "git_node": "1202b0f6632508306acbcd5263a40e81184a1c5a", "git_parents": ["4f5d31103ac192fbbc4ff6659a77d56bdb619dda"], "node": "23ace202386d0894746723eb5cd96d303a8ba0dd", "parents": ["d5ee300bd8c20e62b0280c2c531313fa8f68f04b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930130, "git_changesets": ["1202b0f6632508306acbcd5263a40e81184a1c5a"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27427": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andreas Farre \u003cfarre@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2049049 - Drop unused AutoEntryScript.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D308548\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311518\n", "files": ["dom/navigation/Navigation.cpp"], "git_node": "8e2a22ee5c929a8c91fc6f3842961a848a6dd5e9", "git_parents": ["1202b0f6632508306acbcd5263a40e81184a1c5a"], "node": "1ed8657d7daff754d353f969d12bf64237b10732", "parents": ["23ace202386d0894746723eb5cd96d303a8ba0dd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930169, "git_changesets": ["8e2a22ee5c929a8c91fc6f3842961a848a6dd5e9"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27428": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2052841. Don't taint a same-origin response that a service worker substitutes for a cross-origin request.  a=pascalc\n\nWhen a service worker answers a cross-origin request with a same-origin\nresource (respondWith(fetch(\u003csame-origin URL\u003e))), the response is delivered as\nan internal redirect from the cross-origin request URL to the same-origin\nresponse URL. nsITimedChannel's allRedirectsSameOrigin counts that internal\nredirect as a cross-origin hop, so consumers that use it to decide tainting\n(image loads, stylesheets, media) treat the resource as cross-origin and taint\nit -- even though the bytes are same-origin and should be readable.\n\nAdd nsITimedChannel::allRedirectsSameOriginIgnoringInternal, computed like\nallRedirectsSameOrigin but ignoring internal (e.g. service-worker response-URL)\nredirects, and switch the tainting consumers (imgRequestProxy, the CSS Loader,\nand the media resources) to it. Real cross-origin redirects still flip it, so\ngenuine cross-origin loads (including bounce-backs) still taint. Other users of\nallRedirectsSameOrigin (resource timing, Fetch body-access) intentionally keep\nthe original flag.\n\nAdd a service-worker regression test for the same-origin substitution case\n(CSS).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311498\n", "files": ["dom/ipc/DOMTypes.ipdlh", "dom/media/ChannelMediaResource.cpp", "dom/media/CloneableWithRangeMediaResource.cpp", "dom/media/FileMediaResource.cpp", "image/imgRequestProxy.cpp", "layout/style/Loader.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsITimedChannel.idl", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpBaseChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpBaseChannel.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParams.ipdlh", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParent.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/NullHttpChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/NullHttpChannel.h", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/css-sw-same-origin-substitution.https.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/resources/css-sw-same-origin-substitution-iframe.sub.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/resources/css-sw-same-origin-substitution-worker.js"], "git_node": "3977d7382736d9300fb23149c37fa9f74119eca6", "git_parents": ["8e2a22ee5c929a8c91fc6f3842961a848a6dd5e9"], "node": "c13023c56a1883fb133b7aa16e729cefa95e3ec5", "parents": ["1ed8657d7daff754d353f969d12bf64237b10732"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930358, "git_changesets": ["3977d7382736d9300fb23149c37fa9f74119eca6"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27429": {"changesets": [{"author": "stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2049720 [Linux] Don't use strlen to check D&D data sizes r=jhorak a=pascalc\n\ngtk_selection_data_get_length() returns data len without trailing null char.\nAlso we may get UTF-8 string with nested null chars.\nThere's no point to compare len returned from srtlen() and gtk_selection_data_get_length() as\nthey return different values. Just use data len we get from Gtk, use use exact text size anyway\nas we convert it to UTF-16.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311467\n", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsDragServiceGtk.cpp"], "git_node": "ecb0991bc157f6b1e8f66f6fd80e7778026cd3cc", "git_parents": ["3977d7382736d9300fb23149c37fa9f74119eca6"], "node": "f3ba77223ffca0e40793b6f6f588833bcc0b290e", "parents": ["c13023c56a1883fb133b7aa16e729cefa95e3ec5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930503, "git_changesets": ["ecb0991bc157f6b1e8f66f6fd80e7778026cd3cc"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27430": {"changesets": [{"author": "Stephen A Pohl \u003cspohl@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050002: macOS: Keep the file's extension in the save panel when the format popup is not changed.  a=pascalc\n\nThe fix for bug 514491 removed the code that declared the default filename's extension as the save panel's allowed type, and replaced it with an observer that updates the extension only when the user changes the format popup.\n\nFor a download where the user just picks a location and does not touch the format popup, nothing tells NSSavePanel what the file's extension is, so on some configurations the extension is dropped from the saved file. This restores declaring the default filename's extension as the allowed type at setup, and keeps the observer's allowedFileTypes in sync so the format popup still updates the extension as intended by bug 514491.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310756\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311202\n", "files": ["widget/cocoa/nsFilePicker.mm"], "git_node": "b9f3f44ba7b807b405458352d8cecc96acabdd42", "git_parents": ["ecb0991bc157f6b1e8f66f6fd80e7778026cd3cc"], "node": "488d945b54e3302089e1c63a34f30dc447207299", "parents": ["f3ba77223ffca0e40793b6f6f588833bcc0b290e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930542, "git_changesets": ["b9f3f44ba7b807b405458352d8cecc96acabdd42"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27431": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2050626.  a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311499\n", "files": ["image/imgRequest.cpp", "image/imgRequest.h", "image/imgRequestProxy.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/fetch/images/canvas-remote-read-remote-image-redirect.html.ini"], "git_node": "333f274bfe66f15f934256e572d2c2535a82b83d", "git_parents": ["b9f3f44ba7b807b405458352d8cecc96acabdd42"], "node": "2b29cac68c3f4ca095d5d1618c7f17ed6db10b2a", "parents": ["488d945b54e3302089e1c63a34f30dc447207299"], "tags": []}], "date": 1783930700, "git_changesets": ["333f274bfe66f15f934256e572d2c2535a82b83d"], "user": "pchevrel@mozilla.com"}, "27432": {"changesets": [{"author": "Vincent Hilla \u003cvhilla@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2048851 - Clear principalToInherit in LoadPageAsViewSource.  a=pascalc\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D309163\n\nDif